</para><quote depth="1"><quote depth="2"><quote depth="3"><quotepara depth="3">import xmlrpclib
server_url = '<url>http://rpc.geocoder.us/service/xmlrpc</url>'
server = xmlrpclib.Server(server_url)
result = server.geocode("3745 SE Harrison St., Portland, OR 97214")
result
</quotepara></quote></quote></quote><para depth="0">[{'city': 'Portland', 'prefix': 'SE', 'suffix': '', 'zip': 97214, 'number':
3745, 'long': -122.624652, 'state': 'OR', 'street': 'Harrison', 'lat':
45.508740000000003, 'type': 'St'}]

</para><para depth="0">Try it, if you've got a US address you want to check (then maybe enter the
coords in Google Earth to see where that is).

</para><para depth="0">The server is actually written in Perl.

</para><para depth="0">Kirby
